TWO suspects who’ve been terrorising the community of New Brighton, and who raped a woman (26) in front of her gogo (83), have been arrested. The suspects, aged 22 and 18, broke into the house in Maqanda Street in the Port Elizabeth kasi on Monday night. They were arrested at a house in KwaZakhele on Wednesday. They were found in possession of eight cellphones, including the two taken during the house robbery. Captain Andre Beetge said: “On Monday just before midnight, a 26-year-old woman was woken up by two suspects who entered a house where she lives with her gogo. “They both face charges of house robbery and rape. They will appear in the New Brighton Magistrates Court soon.